EC2 (ELASTIC COMPUTE CLOUD):
    EC2 user data: use to bootstrap our instance (bootstrap means launch command when machine start first)
    ec2 instance types
    launch EC2 instance: EC2 -> launch instance -> (name, key pair, SSH amd HTTP, advance details -> user date (paste EC2 code given))
    EC2 instance type: 
        types :      https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/instance-types/
        comparision: https://instances.vantage.sh/
        IMP types
        1) general purpose
        2) compute optimised
        3) memory optimised
        4) storage optimised


security groups:
    use as a firewall for instance (allow and deny, inbond and outbond of data)
    can refer other sequrity group (means allow data come or go to other other secqurity group)
    Security groups only contain 'allow' rules
    security groups Locked down to a region / VPC combination
    By default - All inbound traffic is BLOCKED and All outbound traffic is AUTHORISED

classic ports:
    22   - SSH      (Secure Shell) - log into linux instance
    21   - FTP      (File Transfer Protocol)
    22   - SFTP     (Secure File Transfer Protocol)
    80   - HTTP     
    443  - HTTPS    
    3389 - RDP      (Remote Desktop Protocol) - log into windows instance

NOTE - if we see a timeout on browser while connecting to EC2 instance. it is because of sequrity group

