    navigate to instanes -> select instance and click connect option -> scrol down and click connect

connect IAM role to EC2 instance
    navigate to instanes -> select instance and click actions -> sequrity -> Modify IAM user -> select IAM role -> Update IAM role

EC2 instances purchasing options:
    On demand
    Spot instance - short workloads, cheap, can loss instance (less reliable)
    Capacity reservation - reserve capicity in a spacific AZ for any duration (GUARANTEE that you'll get an instance.)
    Reserve instance (1 and 3 year comitment) - NOT GUARANTEE that you'll get an instance.
        Standard RI - Less flexible   Higher Discout
        Convertible RI - More flexible   Lower Discout
    Saving plan - comitment of a amount of usage, workload
    Dedicated host - book a entire physical server
    Dedicated instance - no other cx will share your hardware


| Feature                | Reserved Instance       | Dedicated Instance           | Capacity Reservation         |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------  | --------------------------   | --------------------------   |
| **Main Use**           | Save money              | Isolation on physical host   | Reserve compute capacity     |
| **Billing Impact**     | Discounted hourly rate  | On-Demand pricing            | Pay regardless of use        |
| **Hardware Isolation** | ❌ Shared               | ✅ Dedicated                | ❌ Shared (unless combined) |
| **Capacity Guarantee** | ❌ No                   | ✅ (dedicated hardware)     | ✅ Yes                      |
| **Time Commitment**    | ✅ 1 or 3 years         | ❌ No commitment            | ❌ No commitment            |


IPAM (IP address management)
    search IPAM -> open VPC IPAM -> create IPAM -> allow data replication, add all reagion -> create IPAM

