-------------------------------------------------------------------- Lacture 51


EC2 INSTANCE STORAGE SELECTION


EBS (Elastic block storage) volume: (thinks it as a USB storage device that can be connected over network)
    use to persist the data even after termination of EC2 instance
    1 EBS volume can be attached to only one instance (at certified cloud practioner level)
    1 EBS volume is fixed to that availablity zone
    1 instance have many EBS volume attached to it

create volume:
EC2 -> slide left menu and click volume -> create volume -> Select GP2, 1GiB, avilablity zone(same as instance) -> create volume

Note: create volume with avilablity zone(same as instance) is IMPORTANT to attach this volume to instance

Attach Volume:
EC2 -> slide left menu and click volume -> select volume -> attach volume -> choose instance and name -> attach volume

EBS snapshort:
    use to make a backup(snapshort /copy) of EBS volume at a point of time
    take snapshort after detaching with instance is best practice

EBS snapshort advantage:
    can make a copy of volume in another reagion /availablity zone and attach it to another instance
    can archive volume state at a point of time
    can setup Recycle bin for snapshort
    can Archive SS (Restoration take 24 - 72 hours)

EBS snapshort creation:
    EC2 -> slide left menu and click volume -> create snapshort -> add discription and create Snapshort

EBS snapshort location:
    EC2 -> slide left menu and click snapshort

EBS snapshort copy to another region:
    SS -> select SS -> actions -> copy SS -> add description and select region and copy SS

EBS volume creation to another region:
    snapshort -> select SS -> action -> create volume from SS -> add volume type, size, availablity zone -> create volume

EBS snapshort archive:(75% less price)(to restore from archive we have to wait for 24-72 hours)
    snapshort -> select SS -> action -> archiving -> archive SS

EBS snapshort recycle bin:
    SS -> recycle bin -> set up retantion rules
    SS -> select SS -> delete SS (move to recycle bin)
    restore SS: SS -> recycle bin -> select SS -> recover

