-------------------------------------------------------------------- Lacture 56


AMI (Amazon Machine Image):

AMI is the customization of an EC2 instance (think it as a image / copy of EC2 instance)
In AMI we can add our own OS / software / sequrity etc
Faster boot / configure time because all softwares are pre-packed

AMI can be copied to another reagion

we can make a EC2 instance using
    A public AMI : amazon provide
    own AMI: which is buit by our own
    AWS marketplace AMI: make by other (for selling purpose)

AMI process (from an EC2 instance):
    Start an EC2 instance and customise it
    Stop instance
    Make AMI - this will also create EBS snapshort
    Launch instances from AMI

AMI creation:
    launch new ec2 instance:
        Key pair (login) - select key pairs
        Network settings - Select existing security group -> add security groups in Common security groups
        Advanced details -> user data -> copy - paste all code given except last line 'echo .......... html'
        launch instance
        open public IPv4 using HTTP
        if it show 'It works!' means all good
    create AMI:
        select on create instance -> actions -> image and templates -> create image -> write image name and click create image
    launch instance with AMI:
        Way - 1 
            Name and tags -> give name
        way - 2
            instance -> launch insance
            Name and tags -> give name
            Application and OS Images -> My AMIs -> owned by me -> select AMI in Amazon Machine Image (AMI)
        Key pair (login) - select key pairs
        Network settings - Select existing security group -> add security groups in Common security groups
        Advanced details -> user data -> copy - paste code
            '
            #!/bin/bash
            # Use this for your user data (script from top to bottom)
            # install httpd (Linux 2 version)
            echo "<h1>Hello World from $(hostname -f)</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
            '
        launch instance
        open public IPv4 using HTTP
        if it show 'Hello world' means all good


EC2 Image Builder:
    use to automate creation, manage, validate and test of EC2 AMIs (vertual machines / container Images)


EC2 Instance Store: (Ephemeral storage):
    EBS are good but limited performance
    EC2 instance store has high performance
    better I/O performance
    if we stop or terminate EC2 instance than the EC2 instance store attached to it will lose all data 
    good for cache, buffer, temporary data, scratch data

EFS (Elastic File System):
    It is another type of storage
    100s of EC2 instances access EFS at the same time
    work only on linux EC2 instance
    work with any availablity zone in a region
    highly available, scalable, expensive
    pay on storage not capicity planning
    EFS-IA (EFS infrequent access):
        lower in cost than EFS
        automatic move data which is not frequently use to EFS-IA with a lifecycle policy
        automatic move data from EFS-IA if call by instance

Shared responsiblity model for EC2 storage:
    AWS responsiblity:
    user responsiblity:
        backup / Snapshort procedure
        encription
        responsiblity any data on disk
        etc.

Amazon FSx :
    third party high performance file system on AWS
    FSx Lusture: (drived from "Linux" and "cluster")
        linux based
        use for high performance computation
        millions IOPS (Input Output Operation per Second) and 100s GB per second
        task - ML, video processing, analitics etc
    FSx Windows:
        windows native
        connect to Windows instances and Windows infrastructure easily
    etc.

