-------------------------------------------------------------------- Lacture 65

ELB and ASG Section :

Elastic Load Balancing and Auto Scaling Group

Scalablity:
    vertical scalablity - increase the size of instance (t2.micro to t2.large)
    horizontal scalablity (elasticity) - increase the no. of instance (10 instance to 20 instance)
        load balancer
        auto scale group

High availablity:
    run application on atleast 2 AZ (availablity zones) to avoide system down due to any disaster
    load balancer multi AZ
    auto scale group multi AZ

scalablity vs elasticity vs agility (IMP)

Load balancer:
    they are server that forward internet trafic to multiple server (EC2 instances) down stream
    give a single point of access (DNS) to application
    handle failure in down stream
    perform regular health cheacks to instances
    enable SSL (secure socket layer) termination like HTTPS to website
    High availablity accros zone

ELB:
    Elastic load balancer is  load balancer provided by AWS
    Type of EBS
        Aplication LB - layer 7 - HTTP / HTTPS / gRPC
        Network LB (High preformance, millons of request per second) - layer 4 - TCP / UDP
        Gateway LB (Fire wall, security of EC2 instances)- layer 3 - GENEVE protocol on IP packet

CreateLoadBalancer:
    Create Instance:
        creating 2 instance
        Key pair (login) - Proceed without a key pair (Not recommended)
        Network settings - Select existing security group -> add security groups in Common security groups
        Advanced details -> user data -> copy - paste all code given
        launch instance
        different name instances 
    Create Target group:
        select 'target group' in left menu in EC2
        Name target group click 'next'
        select instance want to add and click 'Include as pending below'
        click create Target group
    Create SG for LB:
        select Security group in left menu in EC2
        add name and decs for SG
        Add inbond rules (HTTP and 0.0.0.0/0)
        click Create SG
    Create LB:
        select load Balancer in left menu in EC2
        select aplication load balancer
        give name and select all avilablity zone
        select only SG we created
        in Listeners and routing select target group we created in Default action
        click Create load balancer


Target group:
    Group of EC2 inastance which is use by Load Balaner to distribute trafic


Launch Template:
    Template of EC2 Instance which is Use by ASG to create EC2 instance when need


ASG (Auto Scaling Group):
    add and remove instace according to trafic
    we define Minimum and maximum no. of instance ASG can create 
    almatic register instance with LB

Create ASG:
    create ASG:
        select ASG in left menu in EC2
        enter name and select template then click next
        select or create instance template
        steps to create template
            click 'create a launch template' below
            Launch template name and description - enter name
            Application and OS Images - quick start - amazon linux
            Instance type - t2.micro (Free tair)
            Network setting - security groups - select SG which is used for instance creation
            Advanced details -> user data -> copy - paste all code given
            click create launch template
        Network - Availability Zones and subnets - select all zone
        Load balancing - Choose from your load balancer target groups - select LB(if create previously else create)
        Health checks - Turn on Elastic Load Balancing health checks - tick
        Group size - Desired capacity - enter Desired capacity(ex - 2)
        Scaling - Min desired capacity, Max desired capacity - enter min, max (ex-1, 3 respactively)
        click 'create ASG' at last

ASG-scaling strategy:
    Manual Scaling
    Dynamic Scaling
        Simple/step  Scaling - we define rules 
        Target tracking Scaling - we define Matrix like percentage of CPU utilization
        Sheadule Scaling - use time
    Predictive Scaling - use ML

