-------------------------------------------------------------------- Lacture 73


AWS S3 (Simple Storage Service):

S3:
    it advertise as 'infinately storage' service
    use case:
        back up and recovery
        archive
        hybrid cloud
        application hosting
        media hosting
        data lake and big data analysis
        software dilavery
        static website


S3 store files (object) in directory (buckets):
    buckets (directory):
        grobally unique name
        S3 looks like a global service but buckets defined at regional level
    Object (files):
        object has key (key = full path)
        ex - s3://my-bucket/my_folder/another_folder/my_file.txt
        key = prefix (ex - my_folder/another_folder) + object name (ex - my_file.txt)
    object value = content of object
    max object size = 5 TB
    if file size > 5 GB, it must be upload in multi-part

Note - there is no concept of directory in buckets


Create bucket:
    go to S3 service
    click create bucket, give name, and click create bucket

upload files (object):
    in bucket click upload
    add file want to upload
    click upload

see files:
    click on file (object) name
    click on open
    Note - can't open by Object URL because file is private


S3 Security:
    User based
        IAM permision
    Resource based
        Bucket policy - cross accout permision
        Object access control list
        Bucket access control list

Note - An IAM principal can access S3 object if IAM permition allow or RESOURCE POLICY allows and there is NO EXPLICIT DENY

EC2 can access S3 using IAM roles

S3 bucket policy:
    JSON based policy
    use S3 bucket for policy
        cross account access
        public access

Bucket setting for block public access - developed by AWS

Available an AWS bucket publically:
    Go to bucket and click permision
    Block public access - edit - Block all public access - untick
    Bucket policy - edit - copy Bucket ARN and policy generator
    Type of Policy - S3 Bucket Policy
    Add statement(s)
        Effect - allow
        Principal - *(means any one can access)
        Actions - GetObject
        Amazon Resource Name (ARN) - paste copy Bucket ARN and add '/*' at last (everthing in bucket)
        Click generate policy and copy json code
    Back to Bucket policy - paste json code and click 'save changes' at last
    Now anyting in bucket can be access publically


AWS - Static Website Hosting

Create Static website:
    Make sure that 'coffee' image and index.htlm in bucket
    In bucket click on 'property' than click on edit in 'Static website hosting'
    Static website hosting - click enable
    Index document - enter 'index.html'
    In bucket click on 'property' than click on url in 'Static website hosting'


S3 versioning:
    Enable it at bucket lavel
    Any file which is not version in past has version 'null'
    After enable versoning, if delete a file this only create a DELETE MARKER on file 

Use S3 versioning:
    Go to bucket - property - Bucket Versioning - edit - enable - Save changes


S3 - replication
    Types:
        CRR - cross region replication
        SRR - same region replication
    must enable versoning
    give proper IAM permision to S3

create replication:
    create atleast 2 bucket in different or same reagion with versioning enable
    go to bucket which want to replicate and open management
    Replication rules - create rules
    Replication rule configuration - Replication rule name - enter name
    Source bucket - tick 'Apply to all objects in the bucket'
    Destination - enter target bucket name
    IAM role - create new role
    save - submit


Amazon S3 Classes

Durability:
    how many times AWS S3 lost files
    (99.999999999%, 11 9’s) of objects across multiple AZ

Availability:
    Measures how readily available a service is
    Varies depending on storage class

Classes:
Amazon S3 Standard  -   General Purpose
Amazon S3 Standard  -   Infrequent Access (IA)
Amazon S3 One Zone  -   Infrequent Access
Amazon S3 Glacier Instant Retrieval
Amazon S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval
Amazon S3 Glacier Deep Archive
Amazon S3 Intelligent Tiering

S3 Standard – General Purpose
    Used for frequently accessed data
    Low latency and high throughput
    Sustain 2 concurrent facility failures (for ex: 2 AZ fail at same time)
    Use Cases: Big Data analytics, mobile & gaming applications, content distribution…

S3 Storage Classes – Infrequent Access
    For data that is less frequently accessed, but requires rapid access when needed
    Lower cost than S3 Standard
    -
    Amazon S3 Standard  -   Infrequent Access (S3 Standard-IA)
        99.9% Availability
        Use cases: Disaster Recovery, backups
    -
    Amazon S3 One Zone  -   Infrequent Access (S3 One Zone-IA)
        High durability (99.999999999%) in a single AZ; data lost when AZ is destroyed
        99.5% Availability
        Use Cases: Storing secondary backup copies of on-premise data, or data you can recreate

Amazon S3 Glacier Storage Classes
    Low-cost object storage meant for archiving / backup
    Pricing: price for storage + object retrieval cost
    -
    Amazon S3 Glacier Instant Retrieval
        Millisecond retrieval, great for data accessed once a quarter
        Minimum storage duration of 90 days
    -
    Amazon S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval (formerly Amazon S3 Glacier):
        Expedited (1 to 5 minutes), Standard (3 to 5 hours), Bulk (5 to 12 hours) – free
        Minimum storage duration of 90 days
    -
    Amazon S3 Glacier Deep Archive – for long term storage:
        Standard (12 hours), Bulk (48 hours)
        Minimum storage duration of 180 days

S3 Intelligent-Tiering
    Small monthly monitoring and auto-tiering fee
    Moves objects automatically between Access Tiers based on usage
    There are no retrieval charges in S3 Intelligent-Tiering
    -
    Frequent Access tier (automatic): default tier
    Infrequent Access tier (automatic): objects not accessed for 30 days
    Archive Instant Access tier (automatic): objects not accessed for 90 days
    Archive Access tier (optional): configurable from 90 days to 700+ days
    Deep Archive Access tier (optional): config. from 180 days to 700+ days

S3 Classes Hands on (Store File in storage class)
    In bucket click upload
    Add files and in property - Storage class  - choose storage class
    Click 'upload' at last

life cycle policy
    it is a policy that define when data is move to another storage class

create life cycle policy: {CHARGE MONEY}
    in bucket click on managemenet - life cycle policy
    Lifecycle rules - create life cycle rules
    Lifecycle rule configuration - enter name and tick 'Apply to all objects in the bucket'
    Lifecycle rule actions - tick 'Transition current versions of objects between storage classes'
    Transition current versions of objects between storage classes - add storage class and days
    click 'create rules' at last


S3 encription:
    server side encription - server encript object after upload - always on
    client side encription - client encript object before upload


IAM access analyzer for S3:
    to review the user who can access to the bucket
    powered by IAM access analyser


Sheared responsiblity model for S3

AWS snow family:

AWS snowball
    Highly-secure, portable devices to collect and process data at the edge, and migrate data into and out of AWS
    Helps migrate up to Petabytes of data
    edge computing - computing / analyse the data where it is created

AWS snowball Type:
    storage optimised
    compute optimised

AWS snow family hands on
    search AWS snow family in search box
    and follow step accordingly

AWS snowball pricing:
    we have to pay for everything except data transfer into aws which is free
    pay for device usage and data transfer out of aws
    pay in advance in case of edge computing
    etc.

OpsHub :
    Is a desktop app to manage snow family device

AWS Storage gateway:
    Allows hybrid storage (on primise and aws)
    Work as a bridge between on primise and aws cloud

