-------------------------------------------------------------------- Lacture 93

AWS DATABASE:

sheared responsiblity model for database


RDS (Relational database service): FREE TIER
    It allows you to create databases in the cloud that are managed by AWS
    Postgres, MySQL, MariaDB, Oracle, Microsoft SQL Server, IBM DB2, Aurora (AWS Proprietary database)

Advantage over using RDS versus deploying DB on EC2
    Automated provisioning, OS patching
    Continuous backups
    Monitoring dashboards
    Multi AZ setup for DR (Disaster Recovery)
    Scaling capability (vertical and horizontal)

-> Load balancer <-> instances <-> RDS

Amazon aurora: (NOT IN THE FREE TIER)
    Aurora is “AWS Cloud Optimized” Relational Database
    Aurora is a proprietary technology from AWS (not open sourced)
    PostgreSQL and MySQL are both supported as Aurora DB
    claims performance improvement over MySQL and Postgres on RDS
    Aurora storage automatically grows in increments of 10GB, up to 128 TB
    Aurora costs more than RDS (20% more) – but is more efficient

Amazon Aurora Serverless:
    On-demand auto-scaling version of Aurora
    Least management overhead 
    Pay per second, can be more cost effective for New apps, prototypes, infrequent usage
    Use cases: good for infrequent or unpredictableworkloads

RDS creation:
    search and open aurora and RDS - create Database
    Choose a database creation method - Standard create
    Engine options - MySQL, tick 'MySQL Community'
    Templates - Free tier
    Credentials Settings - Credentials management - Self managed
    enter and conform 'Master password'
    untick 'Enable storage autoscaling' because i don't want to pay money in case of an error made by me
    Public access - yes
    VPC security group (firewall) - create new - New VPC security group name - enter name
    Database authentication - Password authentication
    click 'create database' at last

Take DB Snapshort:
    select DB - actions - take snapshort
    name SS and click Take snapshort

DBSS actions:
    restore DB  - create new database with same data 
    copy DB     - copy to different region
    shear DB    - shear DB so that it can be restore on another system

Delete DB:
    select DB - action delete
    untick 'Create final snapshot'
    untick 'Retain automated backups'
    tick 'I acknowledge that upon instance deletion'
    click delete

RDS Deployment:
    read replicas
        Scale the read workload of your DB
        Can create up to 15 Read Replicas
        Data is ONLY WRITTEN TO THE MAIN DB
    multi AZ
        Failover in case of AZ outage (high availability)
        Data is ONLY READ/WRITTEN TO THE MAIN DATABASE
        Can only have 1 other AZ as failover
    multi Region
        Disaster recovery in case of region issue
        Local performance for global reads
        Data is ONLY WRITTEN TO THE MAIN DATABASE but READ FROM REPLICAS
        Replication cost


ElastiCache:
    The same way RDS is to get managed Relational Databases…
    ElastiCache is to get managed Redis or Memcached
    Caches are IN-MEMORY DATABASES with high performance, low latency
    Helps reduce load off databases for read intensive workloads
    AWS takes care of OS maintenance / patching, optimizations, setup, failure recovery and backups, etc

-------------------------------------------------------------------- Lacture 99

DynamoDB
    Fully Managed Highly available with replication across 3 AZ
    NoSQL database - not a relational database
    Scales to massive workloads, distributed “SERVERLESS” database
    DynamoDB is a KEY/VALUE DATABASE

DynamoDB Accelerator - DAX
    Cache only for DynamoDB
    Fully Managed in-memory cache for DynamoDB
    10x performance improvement – single- digit millisecond latency to microseconds latency
    DAX is only used for and is integrated with DynamoDB, while ElastiCache can be used for other databases

create DynamoDB table:
    search and open DynamoDB - click on create table
    Table details - Table name - enter name
    set Partition key (for record identification)

Add item to DynamoDB table - click create items in table

DynamoDB – Global Tables
    Make a DynamoDB table accessible with low latency in multiple-regions
    Active-Active replication (READ / WRITE TO ANY AWS REGION)


