CloudFormation
    CloudFormation is a declarative way of outlining your AWS Infrastructure, for any resources
    CloudFormation creates declared Infra, in the right order, with the exact configuration that you specify

Benefits of AWS CloudFormation
    Cost:
        You can estimate the costs of your resources using the CloudFormation template
        In Dev, you could automation deletion and recreated (according to time)
    Infrastructure as code
    Productivity
    Supports (almost) all AWS resources:

create CloudFormation stack:
    set ragion as US-east-1 (due to downloaded code)
    create stack
    Specify template - Upload a template file - choose file
    choose '1-ec2-with-sg-eip.yaml' in given code
    enter 'Stack name' and 'SecurityGroupDescription'
    click 'submit' at last

delete CloudFormation stack will delete all the resource allocate to it.

AWS Cloud Development Kit (CDK):
    Define your cloud infrastructure using a familiar language: (JavaScript/TypeScript, Python, Java, and .NET)
    The code is “compiled” into a CloudFormation template (JSON/YAML)
    You can therefore deploy infrastructure and application runtime code together
        Great for Lambda functions
        Great for Docker containers in ECS / EKS

AWS Elastic Beanstalk
    Beanstalk = PLATFORM AS A SERVICE (PaaS) 
    Elastic Beanstalk is a developer centric view of deploying an application on AWS (use EC2, ASG, ELB, RDS, etc…)
    Support for many platforms (including python)
    Three architecture models: 
        Single Instance deployment: good for dev 
        LB + ASG: great for production or pre-production web applications 
        ASG only: great for non-web apps in production (workers, etc..)
    Elastic Beanstalk – Health Monitoring

create Elastic Beanstalk environment:
    Elastic Beanstalk - create environment
    Environment tier - Web server environment
    enter name - Application name and Environment name
    Platform - python
    Service role - choose/create
    EC2 instance profile - choose/create
    create at last

open Domain to see website


AWS CodeDeploy:
    To deploy our application automatically EC2 INSTANCES and ON-PREMISES SERVERS (HYBRID SERVICE)
    CodeDeploy is use to upgrade code in AWS and on-premise from one version to another version
    Instances / server must be provisioned and configured with the CodeDeploy agent before deployment
    This ensures the agent is ready to receive and execute deployment instructions from CodeDeploy.

CodeCommit – Important – Deprecation
    On July 25th 2024, AWS abruptly discontinued CodeCommit
    AWS recommends to migrate to an external Git solution 3rd party
    For this course:
    CodeCommit might still appear at the exam (for now)
    Every time I mention CodeCommit, assume there’s a GitHub integration 

AWS CodeCommit
Source-control service that hosts Git-based repositories
Benefits:
    Fully managed
    Scalable & highly available
    Private, Secured, Integrated with AWS

AWS CodeBuild
    Compiles source code, run tests, and produces packages that are ready to be deployed
    Benefits:
        Secure
        Fully managed, serverless
        Pay-as-you-go pricing – only pay for the build time

AWS CodePipeline
    Orchestrate the different steps to have the code automatically pushed to production
    Basis for CICD (Continuous Integration & Continuous Delivery)
    ex - Code => Build => Test => Provision => Deploy
    Benefits:
        Fully managed
        Fast delivery & rapid updates
        compatible with CodeCommit, CodeBuild, CodeDeploy, Elastic Beanstalk, CloudFormation, GitHub, etc

AWS CodeArtifact
    Software packages depend on each other to be built (also called code dependencies), and new ones are created
    Storing and retrieving these dependencies is called artifact management
    Traditionally you need to setup your own artifact management system
    CodeArtifact is a secure, scalable, and cost-effective ARTIFACT MANAGEMENT for software development
    Works with common dependency management tools such as Maven, Gradle, npm, yarn, twine, pip, and NuGet
    DEVELOPERS AND CODEBUILD CAN THEN RETRIEVE DEPENDENCIES STRAIGHT FROM CODEARTIFACT

AWS Systems Manager (SSM)
    Another HYBRID AWS service (Helps you manage your EC2 and On-Premises systems at scale)
    Get operational insights about the state of your infrastructure
    No SSH access, bastion hosts, or SSH keys needed
    No port 22 needed (better security)
    Most important features are:
        Patching automation for enhanced compliance
        Run commands across an entire fleet of servers
        Store parameter configuration with the SSM Parameter Store

Systems Manager (SSM) hands on:
    how to connect to ec2 instance without SSH, port 22 (using IAM role and ssm session)

Systems Manager Parameter Store
    Secure storage for configuration and secrets (like API Keys, passwords, configurations, etc)
    Control access permissions using IAM
    Version tracking & encryption (optional)

Systems Manager Parameter Store hands on
    simple

